===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|carpe}} (late 14th century), via {{der|en|fro|carpe}} from a surmised Vulgar Latin ''*carpa'' (which is also the source of Italian {{m|it|carpa}}). The word is of Germanic origin, cognate with Old High German {{m|goh|karpho}}. An East Germanic origin (unrecorded Gothic ''*karpa'') has been proposed, as the fish was introduced from the Danube.<ref name ="OED">{{R:Online Etymology Dictionary|carp}}</ref>

